To find the gravitational potential  one can use either its
integral representation () or the series (). We
used both methods. Integrals () were evaluated using Maple,
while the series () were implemented in C code using FFT
techniques. Both methods give results which agree with high accuracy,
but of course the C implementation is much more computationally
efficient. The function  was recovered by direct integration
of differential equation () by finite differencing in
-direction. The gravitational potential , function
, and their equipotential surfaces for two different values
of  are shown in Figure .



