It is interesting to note that the horizon geometry of the CS-black hole
coincides (up to a constant factor) with the geometry on the 2-D
surface of the horizon of the Euclidean 4-D Kerr black hole. This fact
can be easily checked since the induced 2-D geometry of the horizon of
the Kerr black hole is (see e.g. equation 3.5.4 in)
